1. Go to mogodb.com/try/download/community and install latest (msi)
2. Go to C/ program files /... mogoDb /bin then copy path and define environment variable.
    -- search environment 
    ->  environment var 
    -> go to path and click edit
    -> click new and paste copy mogo bin path and save
3. create folder called data in C: then create folder calledb db in data.
 C:data:db

 Installing mongosh
 1. Go to mogodb.com/try/download/shell and install (zip)
 2. Extract zip and copy files inside bin to C/ program files /... mogoDb /bin.

 Running mongo
    - mongod (server)
    - mongosh in powershell
